    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Terry</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 26, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I acknowledge with satisfaction the
                            receipt of your despatch of August 28, No. 124, together with a
                            translation of a note addressed to you by Mr. Pacheco, informing me of
                            the course adopted by the captain general of Cuba in regard to the
                            entrance into the port of Havana of foreign vessels-of-war.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horatio J. Perry</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
